\subsection{Latent class trajectories of AI-induced job security}
To identify unobserved heterogeneity in employees' perceptions of AI's impact on their job security, we conducted an LCA on the joint distribution of current and expected job security. We evaluated models with two to six latent classes, using the Bayesian Information Criterion (BIC) and normalized entropy to determine the optimal solution. As shown in Figure \ref{fig:image0}, the three-class solution provided the best fit to the data, yielding the lowest BIC value (14,592.21) and a high normalized entropy of 0.803, indicating excellent class separation and classification certainty.

